\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid4467992 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did your mother work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Not to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Not before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh well, she might have done but I - I just don't know what she, you know, what she did, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you know if your father had a part time job as well as the job he did in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well he did - he w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 as the secretary of a - Ancient}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  Shepherds sick club, you know, a - yes, which he did in the evening you know and of course when my father died I did it for a while. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 What did you actually do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well it was a sick club and you see you used to pay so much a - sort of so much a month and - 
if they stayed off work well they would bring - they would notify my father and he would have to pay them so much a week, sick club - sick money you see, and - they were scattered - round about home you know and they just used to hold their meetings in a 
p
ublic house called the Chatham Arms at Turton, I don't know if you know - know of it, no but it - well it's - it's quite the thing now, a lot of people come up there because they make lovely meals you see, up there, you can have a good - a nice big feed a
n
d a drink at the same time you know. And - well of course when my father died I carried it on for a while, yes. We used - it was at the beginning when they used to issue insurance cards you know, and had to collect them and send them - and they - the head
 office was at Chorley and I used to - well occasionally went over to Chorley to see them about it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You don't know whether your mother had a job at all before she was married though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh I should think she would have, yes, but I don't know about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 She never did it after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Oh - well of course I was the youngest of the family you know wasn't I - see I - and I'm sure my mother didn't, I'm sure, because if you look at the - the - yes, at the date they were married 
and then - and the date the first child was born there's only about two years. There's about two years between us all except up 'til my sister that lived here and me there's three years then. Yes. Yes. There - there's three years, as I put on the paper, t
here's three years in - and I only knew that to - well when I was doing, I always thought there was just two and a - two and two and a half years on you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you live at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}83 Wellington Road{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} most of your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well apart from - coming here. Y
ou know, I mean, I never call this my home. Only - well during the war when the blackout was on you know, it was a long way - and you know there was a raid on or anything like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You were telling me that you were the only people in the district that had a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 How many rooms were there in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
We - we'd - we'd three bedrooms besides the bathroom you know, which of course had a toilet upstairs, we had toilet upstairs at the same - and a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 washbasin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  on the - you know, it was really a nice big bathroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 How was the house used, did you use one room as a dining room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Oh yes, we had a sitting room and a - a sitting room and a dining room and a kitchen you know, in fact, we had two cellars underneath where we used to have -
 we used to get two ton of coal at once and - that was sort of - emptied at the door, no, emptied at the - on the steps leading to the house and we used to have to come up about four steps and throw this - all this - carry it, throw the coal down the - do
wn in the cellar you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 How did you sleep, the girls in one room and the boys in one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Yes. Yes. I just tell you too - I thought this might interest you, that my brother and I, when we were very young, used to sleep in the same room as our mother and father you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 There was just the family then, no relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Oh no. No just our own family - well of course there were nine children, well, eight because my - one sister had died you see. But my mother and I were very much
 - with one another you know I mean to say and I - my mother used to tell us about coming upstairs to look at us to see we - if we were all right in bed and she didn't know which was which. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 
Because I used to wear my hair short like a boy with a fringe, cut, just like boys, before they started wearing it long you know and - she used to have to look who had the nightdress on to find out which was which because we were so much alike. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 She used to tell us that anyway I mean -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you always play together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Was there one you were particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Well, my brother, this one - this one here, yes, my brother, younger brother, Fred. You know, I mean if anybody did anything to him like I cried. Not him. Yes. Always the same yes, yes. Oh yes, yes.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did your mother have anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, not really because the girls - the elder girls used to have to do the work you know I mean - they - they used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you all have jobs to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 
Yes, I tell you my job used to be - well at one time we had three bicycles you know, two girls had - had - had - my sister and another sister had bicycle and my brother had a bicycle, but I didn't have a bicycle, but I could ride their's you see, used t
o ride their's. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 And we all - as - all had our own little job to do in the evening you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did your father help your mother in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh father - my father, yes, he used to help. Oh yes. Well I think - on a Sunday we - we used to look 
forward to him on a Sunday getting up and cooking a breakfast for the lot of us you know. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did he dress you and undress you and bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes. When I was - when I was a little girl you know how we used - well perhaps you don't know, 
but we used to wear little sort of skirts with tapes over us shoulders and - I am very sloping shoulders and I used - I used to have to be undressed many time at dinnertime because me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 
shoulder strap}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  had slipped off and you know how comfortable - how uncomf
ortable they are when they get down there like that and - oh he would do all that you know. And I used - I used to go - I used to go to me father for anything I wanted you know, I did you know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did he read you stories and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes. Yes, I tell you about how he used to comb his hair to - he used to say - and he'd nothing on at all you know, it was funny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 He was bald?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes. Well it - yes, we had the washerwoman you know come. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 
In this house, yes. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes, the washing was done at home, and the baking. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did she bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, I can't say she did that. But - I can remember - she used to make flour cakes and whatnot, some people 
call them flour cakes with - or barn cakes you know. And she used to bake Wednesdays and Fridays. She had to being a whole big family like that. And we nearly always had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 cheese}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  and onions for our tea when it was baking day you know, she used to cook them in the oven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did she make beer or wine or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
No. No, we used to drink a lot of buttermilk when we were young. Yes, we used to get it from - in quarts from the farmer you know. Yes. She - what she did, we'd perhaps be - pickle som
e red cabbage but that was about all, you know, I don't ever remember her making jams or that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember what you had for breakfast and what you had for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well we - yes, I can remember, in fact we were only talking the other night ab
out how we used to have the dutch oven - little dutch oven in front of the fire with the bacon dripping onto - on the eggs you know in the bottom. Oh yes, it used - they used to be lovely. Well, yes, they - they used to call them dutch ovens, it was a thi
n
g about that big you see, and - and it had a sort of cover that came over and there was sort of little hooks running across and you used to hang pieces of bacon on these hooks. You'd break your eggs in the bottom of the tin - off the - this sort of - well
 
it was - it was like a tin thing, not enamel really, it was a little tin thing and you put the eggs in and then of course - you used to have it in front of the fire, there was no - nothing like these in those days where we used to have lovely big fires an
d that was put in front of the fire and - well of course the fat used to drip from the bacon onto the eggs and it was very - it used to be jolly good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you have bacon and egg every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Mostly. Yes, we did because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember your dinners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh - we - we always -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Can you tell me how many times a week you age meat and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes, well we used to have potato pies, beef steak puddings, beef steak dumplings some people call them, you know, rolled up in a cloth,
 and if we had - if we were having beef steak puddings we - my mother would probably make a - a - a jam pudding you know with white sauce too you know. Yes. Well we - we had that - we used to have a lot of those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 What about weekends, did you have something special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh we - well we used to have roasts of meat you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 We don't get them now do we,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. We can't afford them. Not like we used to have them. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 
I can see - oh yes, we did, yes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Of course your father was an overlooker, this was a very good job wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Well it was in those days, as I told you, he - he was getting - well when my father died he was getting three guineas a week I think it was or three pound ten, something like that. It doesn't sound a big wage but it was a big wage then, you know, in 1918.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 So you could afford a big roast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 We could afford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember your tea meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes, we used to have mussels sometimes on a washday you know. And kippers and - and that type of thing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 So you'd eat meat every day then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh I think we did, I never remember a day going by without meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember eating tinned meat in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. No. No. No. No, I don't ever remember - might have had a tin of salmon, 
something like that, but never this fancy meat that's going around now you know, sort of luncheon meat and all like that. Nothing like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you always have your meals in the dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Yes. We always had then in - well dining room was in the middle of the house you know. There you see and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Where did your mother cook and what kind of equipment did she have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh, in the - in this back place you know. In the back kitchen, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 And she had a black leaded grate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Grate. Oh yes. And - I must tell you this too - we had - we had a - at one time we used to have a - a fender that had a sort of brass rail all round you know, like this, with a brass rail round - and that was put on the couch, we had a hair seated couch, 
l
ike a leather with hair seated, horse hair you know. Yes, that's right. Well we used to put that on there, we used to spread a shawl on it, put this - this fender on there you know, and that was done on a Monday night and it wasn't put again - back again,
 it wasn't put down again. Oh no, don't - well at one time, at one time, believe me - we didn't have the carpet down in the weektime. No. It was put down on the Saturday morning until Sunday evening and it was often taken up on Sunday evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Would this be in your dining room or your front room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Yes. No, in the dining room. The front room was all right. But in the dining room, of course - we all wore clogs you know. I wore clogs, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did your father ever repair your clogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did he repair them? No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did your mother make your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, because - no, because we had auntie who was in that trade and my mother, if we wanted }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 anything}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 , my mother - she used to send us en bloc to this auntie in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 Darwin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  and she used to choose and tell us what we had to have but the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Well, because he was a - a very - posh dressmaker and she had as many as six sewers and - my mother used to send us and we used to come back and we used to tell her what we were going to have. Oh it was lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You always had new clothes did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes, always had new clothes. Yes, I know I am and - and I'm not disputing that. We all -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 What time of the year would you have them new ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh you used to have them at the beginning of 
May about because - the sermons used to begin you know at various chapels and - and we used to - the first sermons was - a sort of branch of our church, St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 Anne\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  church, was Hog Lane and - and - they were the first to have, first Sunday in May I think it 
is there. Then of course came the - Congregational service - sermons up there and then came the Methodists you know. Well ours where I go isn't until August or the beginning of September. So of course we always had to get them at - early to get the wear o
u
t of them you know. And - we didn't have it no. But I do remember this, that - when my father was working they used to have four days at Whit week and four days in September, that was before we got these week's holidays you know and I - I well remember my
 mother, we used to have a big American case and all our clothes }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11417172\charrsid12015374 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
 put in there for - for all - except when my brothers got old and got girls and - but the others, me and my two sisters and my brother, younger brother, the clothes were put in this case a
nd we used to go away to Blackpool for four days. And we used to go on a train at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 17}}}half past five
{\*\xmlclose} in the morning. To get there quick. And we always used to go Blackburn way because Bolton were on holiday you know, and we thought it would be better going Blackburn way because Blackburn didn't have the holidays, no. We had 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose} holidays you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 And you always went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Blackpool{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well, whist - whilst we were going with my mother and father, yes, that ware - well for four days you can't go much further.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 What did you do when you got there, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Oh - we used to play, you know, we'd always a new bucket and spade you know. Didn't matter how many we had at home, new bucket and spade and a ball and - we were landed you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you ever go away for Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
No, we didn't have Bank Holidays up in the village no. Cotton Mills don't have Bank Holidays, didn't then, I don't know if they - I don't think they do now because when I worked at Irwell Bank -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 This was at Farnworth wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Down Turton way near where Mrs Hog used to work. We perhaps got half day on Bank Holiday because there'd be - nothing would have come in the post you know and there's nothing much to do if you didn't send any yarn away on that da
y or anything like that so we perhaps, well, I know because one time the secretary said we could go home about four o'clock I think it were. Oh, I said, I'm not going home, I've come now all this long way. All day. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You told me you mother had paid help didn't you, she had someone to do the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes, oh yes, the lady - we had the washerwoman. Two and six. Yes. Two and six a day and she used to come at 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}}half past seven{\*\xmlclose}
 in the morning and she used to have her breakfast before she started to wash you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You gave her her breakfast did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes, had her breakfast and she had her dinner, with us, sat all at one table sat you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 What did you call her, did you know who was a sort of washerwoman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh she lived not far from us, Mrs }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 Wa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 lmsley she was called.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 And you always used to call her Mrs Walmsley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Oh yes. Yes. She - she used to stay and - she used to have her breakfast dinner and tea with us and she used to go home about - well, anywhere from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 16}}}half past four to five o'clock{\*\xmlclose}
. It was a full day you know isn't when you think of it. Yes. For half a crown. But of course that was a big - a lot of money in those days, I'm talking of when I was a little girl you see. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did your father used to take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes, he walked miles with us. Well my grandma lived in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 Darwin}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  you see, my father's mother. She lived in Darwen and - he used to love walking over on a Sunday morning and - perhaps two of us, my brother and myself would go with
 him and perhaps my sister that lives here, she would be a bit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11417172\charrsid12015374 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
 getting older, she didn't want to go you see, she wanted to go with the other girls, and then my mother would come by train in the afternoon to my grandma's and then we'd all come home together at night you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you have any relatives living near to when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
No, not really. No. The trams started to run you see and perhaps on a hot Sun - summer's morning you know my mother would dress us, she had to dress us nicely 
because we were going to this auntie's who made all - who made all our clothes so we always had to go perfect you know and - when we - what - like if we were feeling a bit tired which sometime we did if it was a very hot morning, he would begin to roll pe
n
nies on the road and we'd run after them you see and that was how he got us going miles and miles with doing that you know because - we - we like followed the pennies you see, it was surprising really. Well like - honestly when I - I tell my sister about 
the bath you know, I read it to her this afternoon, oh, she said weren't they happy times, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Tell me about the bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well the - we had our own bathroom of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 How many times a week did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh we had baths very often.
 Yes. We had very - baths very often and - as a little girl - when I - my hair - I told you I had it cut short like a boy and as - as it grew - as I was getting a bit older we let it grow, mother let it grow, and I had a marvellous head of hair, you know,
 almost right down here, and my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 two sisters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
, it was their job every night to comb my hair and brush it and clean it, you know, to keep it - yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you do anything back for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well I don't know, I don't remember because they didn't 
have hair like me, in fact my sister that lives here - she's - she had a beautiful - not a lot of hair on you see, I mean I think I've a lot really for my age don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You were telling me about the bath, the four of you got in together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes
. Well you see if it came holiday time the people round about - there were nowhere really you know, what - sometimes you can - you can go to the baths and have a bath can't you, I mean in Bolton they go to the baths don't they. These clothes baths with - 
but - there were no where at holiday time you know, people used to come and see - knock at the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12133844\charrsid12015374 door}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
 and ask if they could come for a bath, specially if they were going on holiday, you know, and - that's how we used to enjoy ourselves, you know, sit in this 
bath. It used to be steaming hot and the window wide open, you know, we had a sort of window that went out - out on a swing you know and - they'd all be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12133844\charrsid12015374 our}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 - our own age you know, perhaps my - when my other sisters who were older maybe some of their friend
s would come you know and - there we were sat in this bath you know and the - one of them would say, turn the tap on, you know, get some more water in. Oh we used to have some fun, we did really, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 O
h well - I don't think - well unless something had happened to them we would change them every week. That was a - a known thing - everything. But - I mean, if - if we'd had an accident or something like that we would change them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 What time were you expected to go to bed as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well really - I can't say we were late going to bed any of us because we were all fond of bed you know, I mean - and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12133844\charrsid12015374 me}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  brother who was the youngest of the lot never went to bed without his father, my father, mad
e him bread and milk. Always used to want him to make it you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Your dad made it, why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
I don't know, he said it was better when he made it. Yes. But - Fred and I we really ought to have been twins I think. And yet - sere so close, yes, yes. Yes. We were. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 Did your mother always put you to bed or did someone else put you to bed?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes, my mother, I never knew anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 At what age did you put yourself to bed, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well I don't - I don't just remember tha
t - well, actually, I - I'm telling a lie there perhaps because - an auntie of mine lost her husband and - she - she - I went to sleep with her for a time 'til she sort of got over it, you know they had no children, and she wanted my father to give her - 
g
ive me to her for her - to beep as her own child and he said, no, he said, she's worth a thousand pound to me, my father said you see. But - he would let me go and sleep with her and I lived with her for a long time you know sort of - but came home for my
 
meals 'cos my auntie went out to work, she had to work because her husband had died you see, he was only in his thirties when he died. He was playing football and got kicked in the back and it sent him in consumption. And he used to go out to - to fleet -
 
to go out on the fishing smacks to try and get him, you know, better. And my auntie used to take me to Fleetwood and I played many hour on the mount at Fleetwood, waiting for him coming back you know, watching for the boats coming in you know and - with t
hat like I used to - my auntie - when she was at home at weekend I always slept with her but not in the weektime 'cos I had to go to school and she had to go to work of course you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you know what age you started putting yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh 
I don't really. No. But I - I shouldn't think it would be very late because I mean - as I say, we - we were always - always keen to go to bed, all of us you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did your mum or dad grow any fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 And they didn't keep livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
No. A cat. Oh a cat. Yes, we had a cat and it used to sit on the doorstep, on the doormat waiting for me brother coming home, you know, it - it was funny how the cat knew the time when he should come home and it was a big black cat; but we n
ever had any hens, dogs or anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you ever get rabbits from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so that you could all have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well I think she - she was - she was a person that would 
- I think my mother would be a person that would go without to let us have it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember your father having more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well - I - I don't remember - I mean because he - I don't think he was a greedy type of man, he - he himself would be li
ke that, he - he would be without to let us children have it you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 
Do you know we used to call a boy in the village because he once said at school, father has the ham and we have the dip. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 And we always called him ham dip through that. Yes, because he s
aid - that was a family that probably couldn't let the children have the - have it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Were you allowed to talk at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well, no, I wouldn't say we were, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Could you choose what you wanted from the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes. No, we could choose what we wanted, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 What if you left something on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Well I don't think they - I don't think the - that any of us did much except one sister and she was never happy unless she left one little bit and even when she married that went on. And do you know, she had a grandchild who's the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Why did she leave it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 I don't know. I never thought - don't know why she left it but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 If there was something you wanted could you ask for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Or did you have to wait until it was passed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh no, we - we could ask for it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Could you ask for second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Yes, if it was something we wanted, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well, yes, yes, we - actually we had a huge table. It was an extension table, you don't see many of them now. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You used to wind them up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, it had a big square and - and the leaves at - two leaves were either side, you know, i
t went - it pushed under if you understand what I mean, like that pushing under there. And we used to have stools to sit at the table, we hadn't chairs for all of us, we used to sit on high stools, you know, the type that they're using now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You had your own place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 We all had our own place, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You couldn't leave the table when you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, we used to ask. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Could you bring a book or a toy to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, I don't think so. No, definitely not. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you all sit at the table for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 More or less, yes, because you see - it was a huge table. It - it was a huge table and - that open isn't as big as what ours at home was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Would everybody be at breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well no, because - no because we - you see - in those days they went to work at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. Well we weren't up at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose} you know. My father used to come home at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose} and I as a little girl used to take me breakfast with these that were working, that had started at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. Yes. Used to take it to the mill which was only something like going down that road there you know and used to try and carry as many }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 breakfasts}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  as that you could. They'd just half an hour to have a breakfast in you know, from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose} to half past, that was when they used to start at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Who served the meals at the family table?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh me mother always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Who got served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 The children I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You were the youngest so you wouldn't know where the young children sat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Fred and I were the - Fred was younger than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember how he was fed before he came to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well I don't - I don't remember that - I don't remember - do you mean - oh I should think we had a high chair for him. Yes, I
 should think so because I mean to say, right - when we all got round this table you can imagine there were eight of us, there weren't much room for - a baby to be perched up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Who fed the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 My mother always - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You don't remember at what age you came to the table or what age he came to the table
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, no, I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Was your mother an easy person to talk to and could she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Oh no, my mother was - she - she - she never - my mother was this type
 of a woman, she had one sister and my mother would - never wanted to take the trouble to go and see her sister but her mother - her sister would always come to our house, you know. 'Course my mother had a lot of children and it - it was hard work getting
 
ready to go you know, I mean, no motor cars or anything in those days you know. But my - my mother's sister used to come a lot, she - used to come and see us a lot. In fact we - we - we're all friends - we were all a happy family, you know, no sort of - q
uarrels or - we - we seemed to love all our aunties and uncles you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Could you talk to your mother and share your worries with her if you had any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well I think so. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 What about your dad, was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes, well I - if I'd ever been in any trouble it would have been me dad I would have gone to. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 He was affectionate too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 How did they expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well I mean to say they liked us behaving ourselves you know, and - and
 I mean manners and all like that and as I've just been telling you - when - when we had - we had - when it was our sermons and we used to have company from Manchester, my father had relatives somewhere in Manchester, I don't know just where, we used to h
a
ve to - as children, used to have to sit on the stairs until they'd all had their tea you know. And then we - then we - we went in after you know sort of - when all the company had had - had had their tea, like we were brought to the table and - afterward
s. I mean, we were never allowed to sit at the table with them, unless there was room for us of course. But if there were any grown ups there they had to sit at the table before we -
