\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes, we all had a birthday. Every one of our family had a birthday. A birt
hday party in the house, yes. Got presents yes. Oh yes, it was lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you have guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Oh yes, we had - we used to have - my age you know, from the school children, you know, when we were going to school, we all had a birthday party you kno
w, but I didn't have a birthday party when I was twenty-one because the war was on you see and didn't get then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Was Christmas Day something special at home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well yes, because we - we had a big family, yes, and I'll tell you what there used to be mostly - galoshes and - you know, }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12133844\charrsid12015374 that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
 was wintertime and we - and we - we used to all fancy galoshes, you know, those - rubber things that you put over your shoes and - well of course nuts and oranges and - and chocolates and what have you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 What did you have for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh we used to always have a turkey. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 A lot of people used to have a goose in those days didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Well I once }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12133844\charrsid12015374 won}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  a goose in a raffle - and of course we had that, we - mother invited quite a number of people to eat this goose up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well I - I - I don't think I should be above twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Was it a church raffle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 From a - some - some of uncle of mine had put - put me in not knowing - and I didn't know but - I - I wo
n it you know and of course she said she'd ask them all to tea you know. Yes. Yes. Oh well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Tell me about Christmas Day at home, do you remember it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well - yes, of course, I mean all my - my - my sisters and brothers used to come and bring their other half you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember Christmas Day at home when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Oh, yes, when we were all at home, yes, a Christmas Day, we used to have a lovely time and at New Years time we always came to Bolton to the fair you know,
 there was always a - an huge fair on in Bolton - on the - Algoods you know. As a child, yes, we did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You used to go to the fair in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Because - they always have a fair in - at New Year in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose}
 you know and it used to be on the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Town Hall Square{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 you know. Yes. Oh well it - they used to have roundabouts and swinging boats and circuses you know and - sort of - circuses and - and these - animals you know. Lions and - yes, that's right. Do you know where the Commercial is in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose} on the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Victoria Square{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
? Well there used to be a; big - a big show there with lions and - and that there and these - all these men dressed up in - gold and silver you know, shouting sort of come in and on the other side was another one and you know trams used
 to run across there and - in those days but just on the - on the fair day they had to stop. And they - they used to - on New Year's day, yes, went just for one day they used to have to stop you know, the trams coming up there and that's what's all this t
rouble about the precinct is, you've perhaps read it in the paper. Tea you know. Well yes, we used to have - go to a little restaurant, it's not there now of course, and we'd have a steak pudding and chips.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 With your mum and dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you have any musical instruments in your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No one sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. Oh well - we sang ourselves you know, I mean, there's nothing I like better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you make music as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. And nothing I like better than a good sing-song. I'm always happy when I', singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you sing as a child though as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes, I - well I used to sing - I used to sing at the Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you ever sing in the evenings or at weekends, sing together as a family and make music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Oh - we - we used to - what we used to do on a Sunday afternoon, after school, we'd all come home and we - home and - sit in the sitting room and me father would take us to the sweetshop and buy all sweets you - buy sweets you know and then
 - and we'd sit much - munching these until it was teatime you know. Then of course we were off to church again at night you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Can you tell me if you had magazines and books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh we had newspapers but not many books, me father wo
uldn't let us read books a lot. He - he didn't like us to read these little magazine things you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did your father ever read out loud to you or to your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh to - he - he would read out loud to us children, you know, from the newspaper 
- from the newspaper. Oh yes, he used to read to us, yes, yes, he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did your parents play games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well I - I wouldn't say, I can't remember that really because as I say my brothers and sisters, they would play games with us you know a
s children because my father and mother of course were getting on you know. Then by - by the time I was young they were getting on you see but me brothers and sisters, they - they would play with us you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you ever remember a funeral in the family and who attended and what type of clothes they wore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 Well I - yes, they would - wanted to go and look at them in their coffin. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Yes. I've gone many time. I've gone many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember a funeral in the family and who attended and what clothes they wore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Well, I remember - this auntie that I told you I went to live with you know, I remember her husband dying but I was only three. But I remember it as if it was yesterday because I can remember this auntie of mine at Darwen and she h
ad a daughter and she was called Nellie and like me and she died when she was five years of age and she made us both purple coats with swansdown round the collar here and bonnets with swansdown round here, and I can remember although I was only three I ca
n remember it quite well and I can remember going upstairs to look at him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 In the coffin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, not in the coffin, in bed. They didn't - you know, they used to leave them on the bed at one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 And you went to the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 I went - yes, oh yes, we went, my - my cousin - my cousin and myself. Same age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember what it was like and what happened afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well - I mean - it's - the funeral was - yes, well, that - I suppose that would be the same, we would have that. Ye
s, yes, came back home, I mean the funeral was just an ordinary funeral - funeral you know but I - we would come back - we came back to a tea, I can't tell you what we had just now you know but I suppose it would be a knife and fork funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you know what the adults wore?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
We wore - as little girls - no, I don't remember - but I remember my mother quite well wearing a cape and bonnet you know. Yes, I do. A cape - a - - a long, you know black cape and a bonnet that cocked at eye like this - yes
, I can - I can remember my mother quite well, I can remember when we were going to Blackpool one day, her going with these on you know and - us children dawdling behind you know and me father and me mother in the front and they kept turning round and sho
u
ting, come on, come on the trains coming, you know and - I mean, we - it's not like a bus, they couldn't keep a train waiting for you you know, we had to be there on time. Mind you, we used to be in Blackpool by half past eight, going on the half past fiv
e
 train you know, I mean you didn't - in as - a quick a time as you do now. No. All these new roads. Oh yes. Oh yes. It was quite a common thing for people to queue up to go and look at people who was dead. Yes. That - and I remember once - we had a cousin
 
who - who - who - her father-in-law had died and she was very nervous and - his people were going to go for mourning you know. And my mother said to me, you'd better go up and stay with Lily, she was called you know, she was staying in the house. She said
,
 so of course I went up to this house and stayed with her and when I got up there she made me up at the bottom of the stairs. He - this father-in-law was upstairs in bed and - she made - this Lily made me up at the bottom of the stars. And all the time I 
was mopping I was looking up the stairs like this, thinking he might be coming down any minute. That's - well - when - when I was three and went to that funeral he had a plate of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 salt on}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  the - on his stomach. Yes, that was kept it - to keep them they said, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 When you were a child were you taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relations and who took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well - I - mostly with my father because my mother, you know, had a lot to do with having eight of a family you know I mean because we ha
d one brother who was a boy - well he was a very fickle sort of - something like Arthur is now - you couldn't put him anything, he wouldn't come an and sit and eat anything, he'd an appetite for that you know, he - he - he likes to come home and just deci
de on something when he comes home what he wants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 And this brother was the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
I - we had a brother the same and I remember my mother used to tell us about - well I knew this was true. He came home from the mill one day where my father worked a
nd I don't know what we were having for the - for our dinner that day but he didn't want it and - my father said, well you either have that or nothing at all. And he went back to work without any dinner. But when he came home at night he ate his tea, I'll
 tell you. Oh he was a finicky beggar. He was real - but I don't say - I think it did him good you know, after that he wasn't quite so bad you know but he came home and he - he enjoyed his tea, he hadn't had any dinner you know but it did him good.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You say your father always took you out, did he ever go shopping at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
No. No, I didn't - we didn't go - my mother used to go shopping and do you know what - do you know what she used to do? She used to come to the school at meet us and we used to ta
ke - she used to take - we - my brother and I used to take a bag with us to school, yes, well to put all the things in, instead of my mother having to carry them in baskets, my - I remember my mother buying seven pound of butter - tub - you know, the tub 
b
utter, well she - she'd have a piece like that my mother would every Friday. Having such a big family. Seven pound of butter. And we used to take this - aye, yes, we used to take this - this barrow to school at dinner time and then it - then we came home 
a
t night my mother used to meet us and we used to go and she'd buy all the - the groceries she wanted, put them in the barrow, me and my brother would bring them back home, wheel them back home you know, down - the road. I remember my mother used to buy - 
b
oxes of Lovelace's - Doctor Lovelace's soap and there used to be three pound in each box and she always got two or three boxes a week, you know, because - well, not only that, she used to put them in - cut them, that was another job I used to do, cut them
 in perhaps a pound bar like that in three pieces and we used to put them in a drawer where they dried out because - went hard you know. That were a job of mine. Used to like dong that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you belong to the choir at the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, I never went in the choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You said you liked singing didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 I do like singing yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 How did you spend your Saturdays as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well - Saturdays, until we got to the age that we - we could go out with other girls, we used to go to 
the shop and I well remember getting ha'penny as a spending money and - we got ha'penny and we used to - go and buy pomegranates you know. Yes. There was a shop lower down the road and he used to have these pomegranates, we used; to go and buy pomegranate
s. Probably - lasted all afternoon picking them out with a pin you know, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You went to church on Sunday, did you have different clothes on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes. Oh yes, we always dressed in our Sunday best, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Were you allowed to play games or work on Sunday or did your parents think it was wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. we - no,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374  me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 auntie that I lived wouldn't have stitched a button on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
 a Sunday. No. No. She wouldn't have - she wouldn't have done anything on a Sunday. But - my mother wasn't quite like that but she was a bit like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did the church run a temperance club and do you remember what it was like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well no, no, but we used to go to temperance meetings but me mother - they were at the Methodist. We used to go to temperance 
meetings in the Methodist because - well they used to get people coming to sing you know. Not sing, speak.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you join a temperance club though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh no. No, it was just }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 curiosity}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You didn't sign the pledge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. No. No. We us
ed to get men coming to speak you know and they were - they were sort of like ministers weren't they, always preaching on drink and that and - well I mean to say, if you don't want drink you wouldn't have it whether you signed the pledge or what would you
 I mean, I - I like a drink with anybody if - if I'm at a party I wouldn't - I wouldn't not have one. I might have two, I might have three if I felt I wanted but I never go out drinking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 This was as a child you went to the temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You enjoyed going because of the preachers did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well perhaps the preacher and perhaps there might have been one or two nice boys there you know. That was another draw, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you belong to any other clubs organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
No, I - I never - I don't - I don't think I was ever in the girls friendly society, I never was. My sister - my sister was but not me. No, I can't think - we were real good churchgoers but - I can't think of - of anything that we joined belongin
g to church like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you have family prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. I wouldn't say we did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Were you taught to say your prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well of course we went to school you s
ee, we were very young and - and - and you know how you are, I remember going to our Sunday school and - I were - we used to have a real good Sunday school and it were - sort of out in classes you know and one teacher - a teacher and the young men too, it
 was worth - it was a real sight going to our Sunday school. Buy there's nobody goes now, only tiny tots now. It was really nice going to Sunday school, it was, but - there's - there's nothing -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember any bigotry against Roman Catholics where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
No. No, because - my - I had an auntie who was a - married a Roman Catholic you know and - and all - all her children went to the Catholic but funnily enough, all the girls married out of the Catholic faith, you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Suppose so
meone did something the rest of the people round about, say at your church, someone in the congregation did something that the rest of the people didn't like, how did they show their disapproval, do you remember them ever making rough music
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 But I don't remember anything like that. No. No. Big Liberal my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Your father took an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. We were always big Liberals. All the - well we - we followed our father you see I mean, no matter what he'd have been -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Was your mother Liberal too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well as far as I know she was, yes,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you know why he held those views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, I don't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember your mother or father }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 voting}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did he help with them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. Can't say he did that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Never at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
No. No. Because I tell you, my eldest brother, he - he was courting a girl at the time, you know, one election I remember it quite well. And I remember it was at that time and - this girl - this lady - gir
l that my brother was going with, oh they were very big conservatives you know and we'd always been Liberals because me father was Liberal you know, you see, and oh it caused quite a commotion between my - my brother and this - young lady you know. But - 
I
 mean it - they didn't - they didn't quarrel you know, but I mean there was a sort of uneasiness between them you know and - because she were Con - well I think it was her two younger sisters who - who tried to sort of boss her around you know, but - it d
idn't make any difference, he married her and - they still got married, oh yes, he got married.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from there employer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you think your father felt any pressure in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Oh I wouldn't think so, no, because - he worked for a big a - it was called Edgeware Spinning Company and I don't know if you know of them but Barlow and Jones who were big people in Bolton, big - had
 big mills in Bolton - that will where my father worked belonged to them you know. It was always -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You didn't think he was under any pressure at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh no. No. I don't think so.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 And he wasn't in a tied house belonging to the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You said your mother didn't take part in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh no, I'm sure - I'm sure not. I think we'd have learned of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You were interested in politics as you grew up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well I - I - when I grew up I was, yes, and as a little girl I 
was always glad to wear a red bow here. Yes. My mother and I - a knock came to the door and my mother and I went to the door and it was a Mr Sanderson who was putting up as a Conservative then for - so we walked to the door with this red rosette so of cou
rse, oh, he said, it's no use me bothering. Conservative this time because I'm just fed up with the Labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Otherwise you were always Liberal?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 I was always - yes. Well to tell the truth for a few years like since me father died I've voted for th
e Conservatives, I've not - and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Before 1918 were you ever anything to do with a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. No, I wouldn't have anything to do with them either because I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 When your parents weren't doing their work do you remember how they spent their spare time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Well I - I never remember really my mother having much spare time. I don't honestly, can't see how she did because - she - as I say the washing was a big day and the baking day, she'd two days a week baking you know, then came
 the weekend. Sort of the meal when we were all at home and all at one time you know. I never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did your father have a lot of interests outside the home, did he go out quite a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, no, no, he never - he - he'd have a walk - there was a lady 
up in - who had a little sweetshop and she - she had just a little table like that, it was no bigger than that, and she had all her sweets in boxes on the table and you could go in and stand there and it were a - it - it was a - it was a little shop where
 
- a lot of - boys could gather in - on a Sunday afternoon and have a drink of pop - ginger - ginger - ginger beer or something like that and - this - she was a very old lady, oh you would have loved her, she was nice, and we used to go in and ask for swee
ts and she'd say, you could say, some of them and some of them and some of them, you know, you know, and - and even when it had weighed he'd say, and some of them, you know. Put you more on, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Your father used to just go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well he used to send us up there you know for sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 But he didn't go out a great deal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
No. He stayed - oh yes, well, no, I'll say this, he - he would stay inmost evenings 'til about nine o'clock or half past, then he would probably cut himself a slice of bre
ad and put some cheese on it and go down to the pub in the bottom and have a drink of beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did he got any clubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. No, he never went clubbing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did your mother ever go with him for a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. No, No, I don't ever remember. Yes, no, I never known -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 She went to the mothers union didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 When she was in the mothers union, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did she have any interests apart from this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, I don't - think so. No. As I say, she didn't because we in those - I can remem
ber us - we used to have lovely white dresses and you know all those have to be got up and we used to wear summer dresses from Easter until September which was a long time because we used to have lovely weather didn't we. Well, perhaps you don't know but 
i
n - in - when I was a young girl and went to school, oh we used to have some lovely days, nothing like we have now you know. Summer dresses all the time and - and our dresses, my dresses used to be - some material, we used to call it brown Holland, much l
i
ke a linen type but it was brown and they used to be smocked all across here you know, all across the bust, and they were lovely. Well of course they wanted washing very often. We very seldom had the same dress on two days, you know. No - my mother never 
had time to go and do anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You always had your clothes made, do you remember where you went to buy your shoes and your clogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes, at the Co-op. Yes. We - yes, well we had a little Co-op. He was a big tall man and he was a grand fellow, he used to have to go to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Manchester{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} to buy them at the Co-op in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Manchester{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 you know. He - he used to buy them and then we - my mother used to trail us up to this Co-op, you know, perhaps about ten minutes walk from where I lived but that isn't there 
any longer and - but - we used to have some lovely shoes, he used to - he was a good buyer of shoes you know. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You used to wear clogs for school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes, yes. I have a pair of clogs at home now, not mine, they were my aunties, but I
 - I - I keep them if I'm doing the steps at the front you know. To get so - I used to get sore ankles because - with it - yes, because the leather came up and it used to bleed - they used to bleed you know my ankles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you like wearing clogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Well they were always warm you know. And we used to clean them, they were lovely, and we had to clean our clogs to go to school every day with blacking. Oh - oh yes. I - I - they - they weren't unsightly at all. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 And then of course - we used to have to and have fresh irons put on the bottom you know but -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Your dad never did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did he ever put leather in between the irons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh - I - I - well I wouldn't - I didn't know that but my - these clogs I have at home, they're not mine, t
hey're my aunties and she's been dead nearly forty years now but you know the irons at - they put on them - well instead of being iron it's leather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did your father take part in any sport or attend races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Footballer. Used to be a good footballer, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did he go to races or anything like that or have a bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, I don't think so. I can't think he would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you know if anyone used to bet round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well there may have been an odd one but it wasn't a common thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember if your mother and father belonged to a savings club or a boot club or a sick club or a funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes, we were members of - we were members of a sick club. We used to pay one at the school. Sunday school. Yes, and - Sunday school
, and it - it just depend what age you joined at, some - some paid a penny, some paid three }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 ha'pence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
 a week and some paid tuppence. Oh yes. In fact it was called St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244688\charrsid12015374 Anne\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
 Sick and Burial Fund and - we - you - if you were off sick you could send a certific
ate - well, tell them that you were off work and they'd put you on your club, call it putting you on your club and - you perhaps drew about six shillings a week or eight shillings. Something like that in those days, well then, when the war came, the secon
d world war you see - it - it was called St Anne's Sick and Burial and of course paid out according to the money they'd paid you see and their age and I know my nephew had the dealings of it and - oh I think I drew about thirteen pounds.
