No, I don't think so. No. Because - I mean to say - I feel that - I've always been interested in me work and I feel that - to get from a - a sort of - a little common office girl if you understand me and to get to a Welfare Officer 
it wasn't bad I don't think do you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You started first of all as an office girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 An - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 How did you get the job, do you remember? Putting stamps on insurance cards were you going to say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes, well I - I did that, yes. But at -
 at the first it was at a little mill down - down near where I live at - it's not there any longer. And - it was privately owned by some people who lived at the top of the road where I live and the lady who lived next door to us, I was wanting a job, I wa
s
 wanting a job and - I suppose me mother didn't know what to do - what to put me - I think they would have liked me to have been a dressmaker really but - I - I - well, I know I'd have been all right with this auntie of mine because she was very clever, i
n
 the days of hobble skirts she was the - one of the first to wear one and walked down in Darwen - walked down the main street in Darwen and there was crowds of people what - you know it was a Friday and she was always dressed very smart and she always mad
e us smart too you know. Wouldn't let us -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You didn't want to do dressmaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, I wasn't keen on - yes, I wanted office work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 What was your first wage, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 I don't remember what it was, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11417172\charrsid12015374 can\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  remember. But when I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 But you got it through the lady next door?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Well, she - she - she was interested in me and she - she - I - as I tell you it was privately owned and the man who owned it, he wasn't married, he had a brother that was married, named John Booth, and they 
- he lived - they lived up at the top of the road and one day she asked him could he find me work, and it was through that that I got there. And then of course the mill was sold and the people who bought it kept me on, you know, and it kept going on like 
that and then - from - from that mill, I think I told you it closed down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you work Saturdays there, what hours did you work, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 I - I worked Saturdays yes, I've worked Saturdays - yes, and - and also when I went - when I worked in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose} I went to a mill in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose} because - a mill by the cemetery at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose} and - I worked Saturdays then and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you get holidays with pay at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. No, not then. Well, yes, at Irwell Bank I did. Yes. I mean that was - holidays with pay wasn't -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember what your first wage was though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, I don't but I'll tell you what me first wage was when I went down there, thirty-six shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 What year would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 I don't know. Oh I've worked there over thirty years. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 But you don't remember your first starting wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, I - no, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you have a part time job while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. No. No, because I - I got - I was able to help my mother you see, the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You always gave her your money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Yes, I was able to help my mother with - the work you see, rather - with us having a big family - rather than going out to work you see. Part time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 But when you went to work you always gave your wage to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes. Ye
s, oh yes, we - always gave - well, I - I think all our family did, it wasn't a case of - keeping your wage and buying your own things like a lot of people do, no, we never did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 How did your employer treat you at your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh, good. I
've been in - I've been - I left this mill once. I think I told you about I worked at a mill in - then I went to a work - a place in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose}
. I was out of work for perhaps - two months, something like that, and then the man who was the liquidator at this mill in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose} sent for me to go to this mill in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
Bolton{\*\xmlclose}, you see. Well I worked there a few years, I just can't tell you how long, and then that went in liquidation and the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You liquidated every mill you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Three mills I've been, yes. 
Well then from that mill in Bolton the man who liquidated that was a - he was a - Manchester man called Skinner, Colin Skinner, and he - he wrote for me, they - they were having some - calling - making a call of share money down at Irwell Bank and that wa
s
 how I got there. And when I got there I only went temporary but - it eventually - I was there so long 'til then it came time to leave - the - the secretary said to me he didn't want me to leave, he wanted to find me a job which he did and took me in the 
general office doing wages and what have you, which I used to enjoy and we had three mills down there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 This was in Farnworth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 In - Featherstone, yes. And then after that - when what job was - when - the man who was the secretary then of course h
e died and - he said like he'd always - I'd always been satisfactory. Well then when it came to - a time of putting welfare officers on they asked me would I like to have it you see. And - yes. Personnel officer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You've always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12133844\charrsid12015374 enjoyed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  your work have you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Always. Never been any trouble for me to go to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You said you always liked the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Yes. Oh - in between time I - I must tell you this - I - I left Irwell Bank once to go and work for Pilkingstons in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bolton{\*\xmlclose},
 the motor people. And - oh it was - it was - kind of murder after being at Irwell Bank because it was a place - Irwell Bank was very - it was very nice to work for, you were never tied down. But of course they were all - all workers who - who worked you 
k
now, I mean there were no shirkers if you understand, and - and I think they - they don't have to bother you if you do your work do they like that. And then - well, so I went to this Pilkingtons, I - for more money. And - I worked there eleven months and 
i
n the mean - I went down to Irwell Bank to see them, I left them in quite good - on good terms you know - and it came a Bank Holiday which I'm telling you we never got Bank Holidays and I went down to Irwell Bank and the secretary then which was a new sec
r
etary said to me, would you like to come back Nell to work here? I said, why? He said, you can come back if you want. So I did. I'd only worked at this motor place eleven months. And the man at the motor place thought I was very foolish going back to a co
tton mill. 'Cos he said I could have made a name for myself with him you see, I was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You mean you preferred the company in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh - I - I preferred the company in the office down here you know - to - to being in the motor trade really and 
- so with that I decided to leave. Well of course when I went back I got more money again down here you see. Which leaving both places did - didn't do me any harm because I got two rises you see, then of course when I was made welfare officer I got more m
oney again you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you have to serve an apprenticeship period when you were learning office work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12133844\charrsid12015374 
No, just - you know - as a rule you - you generally began at the bottom sort of making up the invoices and posting them off and - and that's w
hat you do and probably stamping them and what have you, you know, doing all the mugging work I called it you know and then of course each - as you go on they - they sort of - teach you how to do wages and - if there's - if you've anything about you. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 I used to like doing wages very much. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You loved the job didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh I did, yes, very - I was very happy. And I was there all - when the war broke out you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 When you first started there did you have to join a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Never were in a trade union at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Did you feel that there was a division of interest among workers? Some people say in those days there was a great division between craftsmen and workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes. Well yes - yes, because I
 mean to say the craftsmen felt that they've had to sort of - they worked for a low wage you know and then they - they sort of - when they came to be qualified well then they got more money and - and there's - there's always that trouble going on now you 
know, I think that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You felt there was a big difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did going out to full time work change your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, I - I thoroughly enjoy - see, honestl
y I'd be telling you a lie if I said, I - I don't think there was ever a day I went to work and didn't want to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 But did it change your attitude to life, did you feel suddenly grown up or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well, I felt grown up and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You still lived at home did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Oh yes. Yes. Well I came here during the war because of - of going home in the dark. Oh yes. Well I wasn't working at Kearley in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you think going out to work changed your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, I don't think so. No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you still keep up your church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes, do you know, when I lived here -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12133844\charrsid12015374 When you were growing up in your teens how did you spend your spare time now, you said you played dolls' houses and things like that?}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Yes, but - well - well when we were growing up we used to go to dances, we had a lot of dances at the school you know, yes, we - we used to get a lot - have a lot of dances.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you make new friends at the mill or did you keep your old friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well, we didn't make any friends here because you see - well I did make friends here but they weren't much use to me because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You still kept your church friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes. Oh we used to have dances at a - a Conservative club and up at the church school we - yes, oh we did, we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did you take your friends home, did your parents want to see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes, took 'em - yes. Well they - they more or less knew everybody that I was with you know. And - and if ever I did hav
e a friend, well there's - there's a girl now, a woman rather that works at a - she did work - she works -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 So you still kept your church friends when you were growing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Did your mum and dad made you come in by a certain time still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Well I don't remember them - me mother and father but me mother really expected it when me father wasn't there. I remember going to a theatre once with a friend - a - a gentleman friend - and I really truly did enjoy - I'd had a lovely evening
 and when I came home my mother grumbled at me. And I think that's about the only time I ever remember her grumbling you know. About the time. But I couldn't come home because I -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Many people divide society into different social classes and groups, i
n the time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one group and some to others and can you tell me what the different ones were? Did you think of society being different when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well - we always used to say - when - when
 I was a girl we used to say - we used to - about some people that they were the gentry, if that's what you mean. Yes, well you - we used to sort of look up to people, certain people, not a - a lot but we did used to sort of look up and - and - and look u
p to them and think they were sort of better than us, yes, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Well, because they were - appeared to be richer you know. I mean they were people probably who had mills and - a - a - mill owners but yet they'd more or less come down to 
our level you know - the mills had to give up and - and - they're not sort of rich any more but used to be you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember anyone in your district whom you used to say, oh she's a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes, I do. She - she was a real lady too,
 her people - I don't know what her people - her father used to do but - she was good looking, she was tall, she'd everything you know. I used to love watching her - her come to church on a Sunday morning 'cos she used to be dressed so beautiful and she u
sed to walk with an umbrella rolled up umbrella you know and - she was - just like a piece of Dresden china I used to think. Used to look at her and think. Well she - married - during the second world war - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember anyone who was referred to as a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes I do because - well - well it just all depends what you mean by a gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember anyone saying, oh he's a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12133844\charrsid12015374 real}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh well yes, I - I mean I've said it, I remember - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 As a child before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Well - I - I was only - I was only - well - what time - I was only twenty-one, it must have been mustn't it. You see, I remember - I had appendicitis, I was very ill and I - I went - I went up to a doctor, I was in this office and I wasn't 
very - had to go -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Was this before 1918 too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You were telling me about the man with the mud pies, you thought he was a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes. Yes. Well - not - well, yes, and I mean - you know, to see him walking on
 the road you can - I mean I know - I know good looking man doesn't make a gentleman does it but - if I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Even as a child you thought he was a gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh yes, I did, I used to like him, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 When you were a child what class would you say you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Well I - I wouldn't say we were amongst the wealthy class at all, you know, I would say a sort - we weren't poor, no, I - I never went - I never remember us wanting anything if you understand me like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Your dad was never out of work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh no, I never - never remember him being out of work. No. No, no, he was never out of work. Really, as I tell you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You never felt your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, I can't say that - no, no. No because - my
 mother was careful, she didn't spend money silly, you know, and then of course when they all got working it wasn't too bad - really. We - no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Which class would you think you belonged to yourself then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well I would say the middle class you know
, I mean there are only two classes now aren't there, the - you're either poor or - but there were no poor people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Who in those days would you think belonged to the middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well, yes, we always felt, that we belonged, you know, we always felt that we were nicely off if you understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12133844\charrsid12015374 What kind of people would you think belonged to the same class as you?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes, yes. Well - well I don't know I'm sure. Sort of - you see, just - just round about me they were - in fact the man we live
d - worked next - lived next door to us at one time, he was a boss at the cotton spinning mill like my father was you know but in the cardroom over the women, you see, my father was over the men and - now - although he was a boss I didn't - connect him wi
t
h us, you know what I mean. He - they'd only two boys but they were - they were Catholics funnily enough but - they never seemed to be - they never seemed to be sort of well dressed or anything like that you know. I don't know - what their means were at a
ll like - I - I can't say but - sort - well - at one - you don't find that, although there are no middle - you - there are no poor people I don't think these days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember poor people when you were a child? Do you remember any poverty at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Well, yes, I know - I know there were lots of people down - they were - they were very poor people a lot of poor people, 'course they all had big families you see and if you don't - if you didn't have a man - a husband with a good wage well then - the
y were bound to be poor. You see, as I said, with my father, he - he got that - he got that three guineas which at that time was a good wage you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 When you were young was there anyone you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember anyone referring to your father in this way or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you ever remember being told to treat some people differently from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Curtsey to them or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You were taught to show respect to those people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Well no, no, no, don't - I mean - now - I mean even -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you think your mother saw herself belonging to a certain class at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well I wouldn't think so because my mother wasn't that type of a person, you know. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you think she and your dad had the same attitude to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well I think so, yes, I think so, I would say so, yes. I would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Who were considered the most important people in your district, do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Well, yes, there were these people Walkers that - had a weaving shed you know which was a relative of this man that I thought was a gentleman. Well - and then there was the Booths who - found me work at this mill you know, they - they were mill owners
, you see, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 So }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12133844\charrsid12015374 mill owners}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  were the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well I should think so myself, yes. Yes. We sort of - looked -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember who the mill owners mixed with, who the employers mixed with, you'd come into contact with them wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well I - I never knew them to mix with anybody, you know, anybody that worked in the mill if you understand me like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 They stayed amongst themselves you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 What about the clergy, do you remember who they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12133844\charrsid12015374 mixed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh I - our vicar when I was young he - he - he didn't caf\'e9
 who he mixed with, he went about with a Catholic priest and - they were the best of - they were like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember who the teachers mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well - the teachers you see, they - they weren't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 You mean the teachers came from outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. You mean the - the schoolteachers. Yes, they came from outside, came from - we - we never - we never - teachers from -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 So you wouldn't know who they mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 I didn't know, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember any shopkeepers and who they mixed with as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Where you lived were all the people in the working class, would they all have the same standard of living or do you think there would
 be different standards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 I should - I would - I would think so, I would think so. Yes, I would think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you think one class felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Well you do come across odd ones you know, in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 As a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Oh well no I can't say that when }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12133844\charrsid12015374 I was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid135013\charrsid12015374  a child, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Were some families thought of as rough and some as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. Yes. some - you come across - as a matter of fact -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 The people in the bottom you were talking about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12133844\charrsid12015374 Yes, well they wer
e a bit rough, you know, I mean - there was a - a - a family in - down in - that - they - the boys used to drink a lot and - and a family up in the village, the boys used to drink a lot and they always ended up in a fight on a Saturday night. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 And I can rem
ember as a little girl we used to - if they knew this fight was going we used to run up - run up and have a look at them you know. Yes, my friend - I have a friend, she said, oh Nellie, I never knew anybody like you, kind of - it was some bother going on 
I always want to go and see what it's all about you know, but she doesn't, she - you know - sort of wants to go further away than - than - than go near. I always - yes, I used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 These people who were considered rough, do you know what their homes were like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Well - these that I', telling you about. Well one - one - party probably would be a rough type of people - people you know, but the other, no, I wouldn't say they were rough sort of people but - but it - I don't know, they used to sort of - 
it always used to be on a Saturday night, never in the week time. Probably they just got enough - too much to drink you know and they argued with one another, then it all - always ended up in a - in a fight you know. I - I - no, I - I - I never went in an
y of their homes, I don't know but I should think that one of them would have a - a fairly decent home you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you think when you were a child it was possible to move up in the world? And do you remember anyone who did and how do you think they di
d it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
Well - I - I - now I'll tell - now the girl who lives next door to me - from here you know - she was married before she came to live next door to me but the people who owned that house was an old couple and I said to the girl, the daughter who 
had it for sell I said, I hope - I knew they were people were after it, so I said, I hope -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 When you were a child do you remember anyone who went up in the world and how they did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No, I - no, I can't say that I do luv, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Do you remember anyone who went down in the world and what caused it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 No. No, I can't - I can't answer that I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 When you were a child do you remember what sort of people went to chapel and what sort of people went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12133844\charrsid12015374 Well - yes,
 I think I - I think - describing like that perhaps I do, you know because we, who went to church, always thought that little bit above the Methodists you know.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4467992 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 Why did you feel this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11339190 NT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135013\charrsid12015374 I don't know. I don't know. You're asking me something now. I
 don't know why. But - we did always feel that we were better than the Methodists you know. I must - don't know, I don't know why. Whether it was because we thought the church was the highest, the top you know. But even the Methodists now -
